resources.description: In order to further investigate the effects of temperature changes on hydrology at basin scale, the coupled model SSiB4T/TRIFFID (the biophysical/dynamic vegetation model coupled with TOPMODEL) is employed to conduct numerical simulations of the impacts of climate changes on vegetation and hydrology of the Suomo basin located in the upper reaches of the Yangtze River.
resources.name: Responses of Vegetation and Hydrology to Climate Changes: Simulations over the Suomo Basin

name: responses-of-vegetation-and-hydrology-to-climate-changes-simulations-over-the-suomo-basin
notes: In order to further investigate the effects of temperature changes on hydrology at basin scale, the coupled model SSiB4T/TRIFFID (the biophysical/dynamic vegetation model coupled with TOPMODEL) is employed to conduct numerical simulations of the impacts of climate changes on vegetation and hydrology of the Suomo basin located in the upper reaches of the Yangtze River. The impacts of climate changes on runoff and evaporation are analyzed.  http://www.j-es.org/paperInfo.aspx?ID=1252
title: Responses of Vegetation and Hydrology to Climate Changes: Simulations over the Suomo Basin
